-+# Game Journey Master Plan
-+
-+Authoritative status: This document is the current planning source of truth for Game Journey buckets and their intended creator workflow.
-+
-+Current completion placeholder: xxx%
-+
-+Implementation boundary:
-+- Do not calculate completion yet.
-+- Do not implement runtime behavior yet.
-+- Do not implement database changes yet.
-+- Do not use this document as a live runtime contract until a later PR explicitly promotes it into a declared registry or data source.
-+
-+Product frame:
-+- Game Foundry Studio creator loop: Build · Play · Share.
-+- Game Hub owns game identity, game status, Game Progress, and Launch Progress.
-+- Game Crew is game-level assignment.
-+- Studio Team is account-level roster.
-+- Vector Art is the MVP graphics path.
-+- Events are the Rules implementation path.
-+- DEV, IST, UAT, and PROD are deployment targets for release validation, not gameplay behavior switches.
-+
-+Completion placeholder rule:
-+- Every bucket displays `xxx%` until a later implementation PR introduces Planned Count, Completed Count, and Auto-calculated %.
-+- `xxx%` is display-only planning text.
-+
-+Bucket order:
-+001 Idea
-+002 Create
-+003 Design
-+004 Graphics
-+005 Audio
-+006 Objects
-+007 Worlds
-+008 Interface
-+009 Controls
-+010 Rules
-+011 Progression
-+012 Play Test
-+013 Publish
-+014 Share
-+
-+## 001 Idea
-+
-+Friendly Description: Dream, brainstorm, and explore
-+Completion Placeholder: xxx%
-+Required For MVP: N
-+Can Skip: Y
-+Purpose: Capture early concepts, audience ideas, themes, rough mechanics, references, and open questions before a game record must exist.
-+Accepted Tools:
-+- Idea Board
-+- Creator Learning
-+- Notes
-+- Game Journey
-+Deliverables:
-+- One clear game concept or problem statement.
-+- Target player notes.
-+- Inspiration/reference notes.
-+- Early risks, undecided questions, and ideas to revisit.
-+Completion Rules:
-+- Mark complete manually when a creator has enough idea clarity to create or select a game in Game Hub.
-+- Do not require every idea card to be resolved.
-+- Do not calculate completion from card count yet.
-+Dependencies:
-+- None.
-+- May feed Create when the creator is ready to start a game.
-+L/C/R Layout Model:
-+- Left: idea prompts, tags, filters, and capture controls.
-+- Center: board/list of ideas and selected concept notes.
-+- Right: decision notes, risks, next action, and diagnostics.
-+
-+## 002 Create
-+
-+Friendly Description: Set up your game and crew
-+Completion Placeholder: xxx%
-+Required For MVP: Y
-+Can Skip: N
-+Purpose: Establish the game container, identity, ownership, Game Crew, and basic setup needed before other buckets can produce game-scoped work.
-+Accepted Tools:
-+- Game Hub
-+- Game Crew
-+- Game Configuration
-+- Tags
-+Deliverables:
-+- Game Hub record with working title, purpose, status, and active game selection.
-+- Game Crew assignment plan for game-level work.
-+- Studio Team distinction documented as account-level roster, not the project assignment surface.
-+- Core game configuration choices.
-+- Baseline tags for organizing work.
-+Completion Rules:
-+- Mark complete manually when the active game exists, has a known owner/creator, and has enough setup to accept design and asset work.
-+- Do not create project records from Idea Board.
-+- Do not calculate completion from records yet.
-+Dependencies:
-+- Idea can provide concept notes, but Create can start without completed Idea.
-+L/C/R Layout Model:
-+- Left: game identity, crew setup, configuration inputs, and tag setup.
-+- Center: active game summary and setup checklist.
-+- Right: setup diagnostics, missing requirements, Game Progress, and next action.
-+
-+## 003 Design
-+
-+Friendly Description: Shape the player experience
-+Completion Placeholder: xxx%
-+Required For MVP: Y
-+Can Skip: N
-+Purpose: Define the player-facing experience, core loop, screens, message flow, and design decisions that guide implementation.
-+Accepted Tools:
-+- Game Design
-+- Messages
-+- Game Journey
-+- Creator Learning
-+Deliverables:
-+- Core loop description.
-+- Player goal and fail-state notes.
-+- Screen/flow outline.
-+- Message/text plan where applicable.
-+- Design assumptions and open questions.
-+Completion Rules:
-+- Mark complete manually when the MVP has enough design clarity for graphics, objects, worlds, controls, and rules work.
-+- Messages may remain planned unless the MVP depends on authored text.
-+- Do not calculate completion from document count yet.
-+Dependencies:
-+- Create should identify the active game.
-+- Idea may feed design notes.
-+L/C/R Layout Model:
-+- Left: design prompts, mode filters, and decision categories.
-+- Center: player journey, screen flow, and design board.
-+- Right: unresolved decisions, risk notes, suggested next tools, and diagnostics.
-+
-+## 004 Graphics
-+
-+Friendly Description: Create the look of your game
-+Completion Placeholder: xxx%
-+Required For MVP: Y
-+Can Skip: N
-+Purpose: Define and create the visual style, color language, sprites, UI images, badges, and visual assets required for a playable MVP.
-+Accepted Tools:
-+- Colors
-+- Sprites
-+- Characters
-+- Animations
-+- Particles
-+- Vector Art
-+- Assets
-+Deliverables:
-+- MVP visual style direction.
-+- Vector Art baseline for MVP graphics path.
-+- Palette/color choices.
-+- Required sprite/vector assets.
-+- Placeholder or final images for key player-facing objects and UI.
-+Completion Rules:
-+- Mark complete manually when all required MVP visual placeholders or Vector Art assets exist and are acceptable for Play Test.
-+- Full polish is not required for MVP.
-+- Do not calculate completion from asset count yet.
-+Dependencies:
-+- Create identifies the active game.
-+- Design provides visual intent.
-+- Objects, Worlds, and Interface consume graphics outputs.
-+L/C/R Layout Model:
-+- Left: visual style controls, palette, asset type filters, and import/create actions.
-+- Center: visual asset board, preview canvas, and style samples.
-+- Right: asset readiness, missing visual assets, replacement notes, and diagnostics.
-+
-+## 005 Audio
-+
-+Friendly Description: Bring your world to life with sound
-+Completion Placeholder: xxx%
-+Required For MVP: N
-+Can Skip: Y
-+Purpose: Plan and create music, sound effects, voices, speech, and audio treatment for player feedback and atmosphere.
-+Accepted Tools:
-+- Audio
-+- Music
-+- Voices
-+- Audio Effects
-+- Text To Speech
-+- Speech To Text
-+- Assets
-+Deliverables:
-+- Sound and music plan.
-+- Required MVP sound placeholders if audio is needed.
-+- Voice/emotion direction where messages use speech.
-+- Audio asset references.
-+Completion Rules:
-+- Mark complete manually when required MVP audio placeholders or final assets are present.
-+- If the MVP is playable without audio, this bucket can be skipped.
-+- Do not calculate completion from asset count yet.
-+Dependencies:
-+- Design defines audio intent.
-+- Rules and Events can trigger audio.
-+- Messages and Emotions may feed Text To Speech.
-+L/C/R Layout Model:
-+- Left: audio type filters, import/create controls, and voice/emotion settings.
-+- Center: audio asset list, timeline/preview, and playback controls.
-+- Right: usage references, missing audio diagnostics, replacement notes, and readiness.
-+
-+## 006 Objects
-+
-+Friendly Description: Build things players can interact with
-+Completion Placeholder: xxx%
-+Required For MVP: Y
-+Can Skip: N
-+Purpose: Define interactive things in the game: player, obstacles, collectibles, goals, hazards, NPCs, props, and object state.
-+Accepted Tools:
-+- Objects
-+- Characters
-+- Sprites
-+- Tags
-+- Assets
-+- Game Configuration
-+Deliverables:
